  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Tissue oxygen saturation (StO2) and its recovery during a vascular occlusion test (VOT) will
      be measured in elective cardiac surgery patients undergoing cardiopulmonary bypass using a
      non-invasive near infrared spectrometry (NIRS) machine. The purpose of this study is to
      determine whether changes in VOT measurements occur in patients during cardiac surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
